PARLIAMENT The Standing Committee on Public Accounts (Scopa) held hearings with the South African Broadcasting Corporation (SABC) on Wednesday.The hearings were on SABC's irregular, fruitless and wasteful expenditure.The SABC reported a loss of R411-million for the 2015/16 financial year.The public broadcaster currently does not have a boards.Seventeen names have presented by MPs for nomination to an interim SABC board. Tweets about #SABC OR #SCOPA AND (FROM:@ajnarsee) eNCA